{"id":67193,"global_id":"www.smilefoundationindia.org?id=67193","global_id_lineage":["www.smilefoundationindia.org?id=67193"],"author":"2","status":"publish","date":"2022-12-06 20:53:14","date_utc":"2022-12-06 15:23:14","modified":"2022-12-06 20:53:14","modified_utc":"2022-12-06 15:23:14","url":"https:\/\/www.smilefoundationindia.org\/workshops-events\/parenting-workshop-conducted-under-child-for-child-programme-2\/","rest_url":"https:\/\/www.smilefoundationindia.org\/wp-json\/tribe\/events\/v1\/events\/67193","title":"Parenting workshop conducted under Child for Child programme","description":"<p>A parent\u2019s workshop was conducted at a school in Islampur. The whole idea behind the workshop was to sensitize the parents about inculcating the values of love, compassion, giving etc in the child from a young age. Such sessions for older students are conducted under Smile Foundation\u2019s Child for Child programme to sensitize privileged school going children about positive values like helping the needy, inculcating the values of love and compassion within oneself. A total of 200 parents participated in the event.<\/p>\n<p>Under the Child for Child programme, Smile Foundation visits various schools and conducts engaging sessions for the young minds. It sensitizes children towards various causes and let them realize their privileged status.<\/p>\n<p>CFC currently reaches out to nearly one million privileged children in 900 schools spread across 417 districts of India, every year. In addition, their parents and teachers are also involved in the process. The programme has today reached out to each part of India with the exception of Lakshadweep.<\/p>\n<p>Smile Foundation is an NGO in India directly benefitting over 600,000 children and their families every year, through more than 250 live welfare projects on education, healthcare, livelihood and women empowerment, in over 950 remote villages and slums across 25 states of India.<\/p>","excerpt":"","slug":"parenting-work